 with the inner edge close to the maximum velocity origin\nand its outer edge closer to the zero-velocity outer circumference.\nFurthermore, the gas stream and secondary star are projected on the outside of\nthe disc with the bright spot of the stream-disc impact region on the disc's\nouter edge in the inside-out velocity space.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 18 Jul 2015 18:35:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-21"}
